text.tspan: Pre-History -- Wandering the lands west of the large sea at the center of
the peninsula, -- they would dub it a golden sea after witnessing one
particularly reflective sunrise -- a traveling group of five shapeshifters...
They would defeat the elder white dragon that guarded the icy mountain pass.
Left with empty lands, they needed help in carving arable land out of the
rocky expanse. The dwarves aided them.
One went turncoat and aided the Xadgnians (or wrwym?, timeline?) - thus Ravens.
The area was called Ul, legend stating that it was derived from the
shapeshifters word meaning 'land between two peaks' (l-ul-l) and in time
the inhabitants would call themselves the Ulfaren, the lands' defenders.
True to their name, the society that emerged was deeply attached to the
land and to ritual. Modeling themselves after the heirarchy they observed
in nature, Ulfaren etc etc
- assigned to caste at young age. It's rigid
- and practice survival of the fittest
- but they're not savage, nor uncivilized
- in touch with nature, death,Â strength, cunning
- choose to live harmoniously with the natural world, and by themselves
- rejected much of the tech advancements of the rest of the Gold Sea
- pseudo-communist society where goods & resources belong to the community
- prefer action over subtly, tradition over innovation
- regardless of caste, regard one another as family
Ul's gates remain open to travelers, though the Ulfaren are
characteristically cautious of outsiders, preferring to keep to
their own rather than deal with their neighboring human kingdoms
